articles.description: Rui Hachimura scored 23 points and No. 12 Gonzaga kept the ball out of Jock Landale's hands to end the nation's longest active winning streak at 19 games with a 78-65 victory over No. 11 Saint Mary's on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Gonzaga snaps Saint Mary's 19-game win streak, 78-65

images.caption: Zach Norvell Jr. lobs the ball up to Johnathan Williams who throws down a two-handed jam early in the first half.
images.name: Gonzaga's Norvell, Williams connect for alley-oop slam

articles.description: Evan Leonard scored 18 points and Tommy Rutherford scored 15 and UC Irvine beat UC Riverside 62-52 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: UC Irvine downs UC Riverside 62-52 behind Leonard's 18 PTs

articles.description: Michael Oguine had 25 points, including a crucial putback dunk in overtime, and Montana avoided an upset on Saturday night with a 71-69 win over Sacramento State.
articles.headline: Montana avoids upset, beats Sacramento State 71-69 in OT

articles.description: Deon Lyle came off the bench to hit 5 of 8 from 3-point range and score 18 and Giovanni De Nicolao added 10 points, including two free throws with five seconds left, to help UT San Antonio hold off UTEP 63-59 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: UT San Antonio holds off UTEP 63-59

videos.description: Grayson Allen pulls up from downtown and drains his third 3-poiner of the half.
videos.headline: Allen heating up for Duke with 3rd long ball

videos.description: Duke freshman Trevon Duval gets a steal on the defensive end and weaves right through the Elon defense for the layup.
videos.headline: Duke's Duval converts on layup after steal

videos.description: Trevon Duval throws a behind-the-back pass to Marvin Bagley who goes down the paint for a loud dunk to wrap up the first half.
videos.headline: Bagley throws down emphatic dunk on Duval assist

videos.description: Marvin Bagley takes the lob pass from Trevon Duval and throws down the two-handed jam.
videos.headline: Bagley throws down alley-oop

videos.description: Javin DeLaurier snags the offensive rebound and tips in the loose ball in for the bucket the second half.
videos.headline: Duke's DeLaurier tips in shot after offensive rebound

videos.description: Grayson Allen knocks down his second 3-pointer of the game to give Duke a big lead early in the first half.
videos.headline: Allen knocks down the long ball for first Duke points

videos.description: Duke's Wendell Carter grabs the offensive rebound off the missed shot and throws it down with one hand to extend the Blue Devils' lead.
videos.headline: Carter cleans up the missed shot and throws down dunk

videos.description: Late in the second half, Antonio Vrankovic finds Alex O'Connell behind the arc for a 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Duke offense in rhythm as O'Connell nails open 3

videos.description: Grayson Allen knocks down his second 3-pointer of the game to give Duke a big lead early in the first half.
videos.headline: Allen in a groove early against Elon
